# Example: daily PostgreSQL backup (Story 1.2)
# Copy to crontab (crontab -e) or use in systemd/scheduler.
# Ensure DATABASE_URL or POSTGRES_* (including PGPASSWORD) are set in the environment.

# Run backup every day at 02:00, output to /backups (adjust path)
# 0 2 * * * /path/to/bmad-stock-agent/scripts/backup-database.sh /backups
